attributes.value: Does not respect the law
Values loyalty
Values family
Finds maintaining decorum a silly, fumbling waste of time
Finds the ideas of independence and freedom somewhat foolish
Sees merrymaking as a waste
Sees competition as reasonably important
Finds those that engage in trade and commerce to be fairly disgusting
Believes war is preferable to peace in general
Is dour as a rule
Almost never feels discouraged
Occasionally overindulges
Doesn't stick with things if even minor difficulties arise
Has no confidence at all in her talent and abilities
Is greatly pleased by her own looks and accomplishments
Is not driven and rarely feels the need to pursue even a modest success
Does not feel the slightest need to reciprocate favors that others do for her, no matter how major the help or how much she needed it
Likes to present herself boldly, even if it would offend an average sense of modesty
Thinks she is fairly important in the grand scheme of things
Is easily moved to mercy
Tends to be a bit stubborn in changing her mind about things
Is quite comfortable with others that have a different appearance or culture
Forms only fleeting and rare emotional bonds with others
Dislikes helping others
Never acts without prolonged deliberation, even to her own detriment and the harm of those around her
Tries to keep her things orderly
Prefers to be alone
Poor focus
A feel for music
